### IMPORTANT
Pre-2025-11 baseline unless a post-2025-10 variant exists in embedding_candidates_2025_11+.json.

## Purpose
Strong short-query baseline that demonstrates instruction-tuning benefits.
bge-small is notable for its query instruction prefix which improves retrieval quality.

## Model Details
- Source: BAAI/bge-small-en-v1.5
- Parameters: 33.4M
- Dimensions: 384
- Context: 512 tokens
- MTEB Retrieval: ~51 (notably higher than MiniLM for retrieval)
- Special: Uses instruction prefix for queries

## Architecture
```rust
pub struct BgeSmallEmbedder {
    session: ort::Session,
    tokenizer: tokenizers::Tokenizer,
    dimensions: usize,    // 384
    max_length: usize,    // 512
    name: String,
}

impl Embedder for BgeSmallEmbedder {
    fn embed_batch(&self, texts: &[&str]) -> Result<Vec<Vec<f32>>> {
        // BGE uses [CLS] token embedding (not mean pooling!)
        // For queries: prefix with "Represent this sentence for searching relevant passages: "
        // For documents: no prefix needed

        let encodings = self.tokenizer.encode_batch(texts.to_vec(), true)?;
        let max_len = encodings.iter().map(|e| e.len()).max().unwrap_or(0).min(self.max_length);

        let input_ids = build_padded_tensor(&encodings, max_len, 0);
        let attention_mask = build_attention_mask(&encodings, max_len);
        let token_type_ids = build_zeros_tensor(texts.len(), max_len);

        let outputs = self.session.run(ort::inputs![
            "input_ids" => input_ids,
            "attention_mask" => attention_mask,
            "token_type_ids" => token_type_ids,
        ]?)?;

        // BGE uses CLS token (position 0) as the embedding
        let hidden = outputs[0].extract_tensor::<f32>()?;
        let mut results = Vec::with_capacity(texts.len());
        for i in 0..texts.len() {
            let mut cls_embedding = (0..self.dimensions)
                .map(|d| hidden[[i, 0, d]])
                .collect::<Vec<f32>>();
            l2_normalize(&mut cls_embedding);
            results.push(cls_embedding);
        }
        Ok(results)
    }

    fn dimensions(&self) -> usize { 384 }
    fn model_name(&self) -> &str { &self.name }
    fn supports_mrl(&self) -> bool { false }
}
```

